VALUES ('8e7f148c-145c-4811-af3d-90094d5eb7ad', 'The student wants to emphasize the most empirically supported approach documented in the notes. Which choice most effectively synthesizes relevant information to accomplish this goal?', '• Turbine prototype 5001 employs tubercle-inspired blade geometry modeled on humpback whale fins
• Field tests documented twelve-percent efficiency gains at moderate wind speeds
• Conventional flat-blade designs underperformed at identical wind speeds in controlled comparisons
• Overnight noise monitoring confirmed compliance with local residential ordinances', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"In intervention 5001, structured pair discussion outperformed silent worksheets, producing a twelve-point comprehension gain linked to evidence-based classroom observations.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Synthesizes the notes to highlight the approach associated with the largest measured gain and supporting teacher observations."},{"id":"B","text":"Whale-fin tubercles inspired numerous unrelated inventions that the notes never mention, evaluate, or compare methodologically.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Imports information absent from the notes and fails to compare instructional methods on empirical grounds."},{"id":"C","text":"Worksheets remain the only pedagogically valid tool because they require silent individual focus regardless of measured outcome differences.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Directly contradicted by the notes, which report substantially larger gains for discussion than for worksheets."},{"id":"D","text":"Comprehension scores are immutable when instructional methods vary within the same curricular unit and assessment window.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Contradicted by reported score changes for both cohorts documented in the notes."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'The notes compare two instructional approaches and report unequal gains favoring structured discussion. The passage anchors the correct choice in language such as "• Turbine prototype 5001 employs tubercle-inspired blade geometry modeled on humpback whale fins • F…", which eliminates options that contradict or overreach that evidence. Choice A is correct because it aligns with the textual logic: x. Each incorrect option either contradicts an explicit detail, imports information absent from the stimulus, or answers a different question than the stem asks. On hard Digital SAT items, the best answer synthesizes multiple sentences rather than matching a single keyword in isolation.', NULL, 'Expression of Ideas', 'Rhetorical Synthesis', 'reading_writing', 'expression', 'SYN', NULL, 'hard', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"hard_content_v2","original":true,"explanation_v2":true,"hard_content_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
